01:46.000 --> 01:53.000
In particular, information is information about objects, events, facts, processes and phenomena of the world around us.

01:53.000 --> 01:55.000
That is, it is information.

01:55.000 --> 01:57.000
The next definition.

02:01.000 --> 02:06.000
The next definition is already taken from the course of computer science.

02:06.000 --> 02:07.000
Slide number six.

02:07.000 --> 02:12.000
In order to give a scientific definition of what information is,

02:12.000 --> 02:15.000
we need to introduce three more concepts.

02:15.000 --> 02:18.000
The object, the environment and the interaction.

02:18.000 --> 02:24.000
The object is something whole that exists in space and time and is finished.

02:24.000 --> 02:27.000
That is, the object is something holistic.

02:27.000 --> 02:30.000
The environment is a multitude of other potential objects

02:30.000 --> 02:37.000
that interest us in terms of their influence on the state of the selected object that we are considering.

02:37.000 --> 02:43.000
And the interaction is a process of mutual change of these objects over time,

02:43.000 --> 02:46.000
when they influence each other.

02:46.000 --> 02:47.000
Slide number seven.

02:47.000 --> 02:50.000
In nature there are two functional types of interaction.

02:50.000 --> 02:52.000
This is the exchange of matter and energy.

02:52.000 --> 02:55.000
These are fundamental types.

02:55.000 --> 02:56.000
Why?

02:56.000 --> 03:03.000
Because all other interactions are based on the exchange of matter or energy.

03:03.000 --> 03:09.000
And here is the question, of course, the law of conservation of work.

03:10.000 --> 03:14.000
That is, the energy that is exchanged by objects does not disappear anywhere.

03:14.000 --> 03:18.000
When objects interact, a certain limited environment arises.

03:18.000 --> 03:23.000
And in this environment, neither matter nor energy is lost.

03:23.000 --> 03:30.000
If one object gave the matter and energy, then the other one changed, because it accepted.

03:30.000 --> 03:35.000
And any interaction between objects, in the process of which one acquires,

03:35.000 --> 03:40.000
and the other loses some substance, is called an informational interaction.

03:40.000 --> 03:44.000
And this most transmitted substance is called information.

03:44.000 --> 03:50.000
This is such a scientific definition of information from the science of informatics.

03:50.000 --> 03:54.000
Two of the most common properties of information follow from this definition.

03:54.000 --> 03:57.000
Information cannot exist outside the interaction of objects.

03:57.000 --> 04:03.000
And information is not lost by any of the objects in the interaction process.

04:04.000 --> 04:05.000
